about natasha avery natasha avery stanford center on longevity skip to content home about about hello my name is natasha avery and i am a freshman at stanford i am interested in investigating how creativity specifically literary creativity changes and is affected by aging although lifetime is expanding the peak creative years of many writers remain unchanged despite the fact that older people retain the ability to write much longer than for example the ability needed to dance a writer myself i often have wondered whether this is linked to biochemical changes linked to aging or perhaps socially construed misconceptions about aging that can be altered if it is the latter unleashing the creativity of older adults could significantly impact the art world and change the nature and notion of retirement i d like to consider this by first examining what actually changes in the brain with age i can see whether the increased focus on emotion in older adults actually positively impacts creativity i can also investigate how social preconceptions of aging could be affecting the literary output of older adults finally looking at some of the older and most prolific writers today i can consider whether perhaps the decision to remain creative actually positively impacts longevity leave a reply cancel reply your email address will not be published required fields are marked name email website comment you may use these html tags and attributes a href title abbr title acronym title b blockquote cite cite code del datetime em i q cite strike strong search for recent posts outstanding examples aging and stigmas creativity for sale music and creative aging fostering creativity existing institutions recent comments archives june 2011 may 2011 april 2011 categories uncategorized meta log in entries rss comments rss wordpress org natasha avery proudly powered by wordpress
